\f1\b0 \cf0 \
- 3.3a2\
\pard\tx340\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\li360\fi-360\ql\qnatural
\cf0   + The speed of flat view improved a lot\
  + The cvsgui tool is now contained within the application package.\
  + The UI is (partially) revamped to better match the Aqua appearance - more to come...\
  + The browser settings are now stored in "~/Library/Preferences/MacCvs Preferences/Settings". \
  + When opening a browser for a sandbox that has been created by MacCvs (CFM), MacCvsX now asks to convert the sandbox. MacCvs (CFM) used Mac lineendings and also used Finder locking as a means to make the files read-only. The cvsgui tool, on the other hand uses the filesystem permissions to make files read-only and can't correctly cope with files that are Finder locked. Also, unless the "Checkout using Mac CR" setting is specified, MacCvsX assumes Unix lineendings. The proposed conversion will take care of all those changes.\
  + some of the command dialogs are now optional - you can choose to only show them when the option key is down\
  + The file path popup (previously available when option-clicking an item in the browser) moved into the contextual menu where it belongs.\
  + external diff support: built-in support for BBEdit, CodeWarrior and FileMerge, or optionally custom application, tool or shell script; there is now the option to view differences from the commit dialog\
  + tag, branch and module browsers available wherever those have to be selected\
  + by default, attempts to use /usr/bin/tcl-8.3 as the TCL implementation; unfortunately, we still require the custom Python framework for now...\
  + moving files to the trash should now always work\
  + many fixes for bugs and glitches - see the file "ChangeLog.txt" for more details\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural
